  "description": "Transparency-log golden vector (RFC-ACDP-0012 §4–§6, §9.1). A five-leaf log on the test registry: leaf 0 is the rcpt-001 golden receipt's publish event (its receipt_hash is rcpt-001's pinned receipt hash); leaves 1..4 are synthetic version-1 publishes by the sig-001 producer, each binding a genuine (recomputable) RFC-ACDP-0010 receipt hash. Pins every JCS leaf encoding, every §5.1 leaf hash (SHA-256 over 0x00 || JCS(leaf)), the tree-size-5 Merkle root (0x01-prefixed interior nodes per RFC 6962 §2.1), a checkpoint signed with the SAME Ed25519 registry test keypair as rcpt-001/lhr-001 (RFC-ACDP-0012 §6 reuses the RFC-ACDP-0010 receipt signing key and construction verbatim), and the inclusion proof for leaf 0 at tree size 5. This is the sig-001-equivalent for the log layer — every log-capable SDK pins it. Executed arithmetically by scripts/conformance-runner.py. Test keypairs MUST NOT be used in production. Values generated by temp/gen-0.3.0-vectors.py.",
